com.rfid

类 RFIDReaderHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.module.interaction.ReaderHelper
      • com.rfid.RFIDReaderHelper

  • public class RFIDReaderHelper
extends ReaderHelper
    The core class to operate RFIDreader.You can send command to RFID reader via the methods. And you can receive the return data via register the subclass of #RXObserver.

      • setFrequencyRegion

        public final int setFrequencyRegion(byte btReadId,
                                    byte btRegion,
                                    byte btStartRegion,
                                    byte btEndRegion)
        Set frequency region(system default frequencies).
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF Public Address)
        btRegion - Spectrum regulation(0x01:FCC, 0x02:ETSI, 0x03:CHN)
        btStartRegion - Start frequency of the spectrum,
        btEndRegion - End frequency of the spectrum,Setup the range of the RF output spectrum. The rules are: 1,Start frequency and end frequency should be in the range of the specified regulation. 2,Start frequency should be equal or lower than end frequency. 3, End frequency equals start frequency means use single frequency point.
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • setUserDefineFrequency

        public final int setUserDefineFrequency(byte btReadId,
                                        byte btFreqInterval,
                                        byte btChannelQuantity,
                                        int nStartFreq)
        Set frequency region(user defined frequencies).
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF Public Address)
        btFreqInterval - Frequency space, frequency space = FreqSpace x 10KHz.
        btChannelQuantity - Frequency Quantity, this quantity includes the start frequency, if set this byte to 1, it means use start frequency as the single carrier frequency . This byte should be larger than 0.
        nStartFreq - Start Frequency, the unit is KHz. Set the start frequency with hex format, for example, 915000KHz = 0D F6 38 KHz.
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • setBeeperMode

        public final int setBeeperMode(byte btReadId,
                               byte btMode)
        Set Buzzer behavior.
        Buzzer behavior 0x02(Beep after every tag has identified) occupies CPU process time that affects anti-collision algorithm significantly. It is recommended that this option should be used for tag test.
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF Public Address)
        btMode - Buzzer behavior(0x00:Quiet, 0x01:Beep after every inventory round if tag(s) identified, 0x02:Beep after every tag has identified.)

        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • inventory

        public final int inventory(byte btReadId,
                           byte btRepeat)
        Inventory Tag.
        When reader gets this command, the inventory for EPC GEN2 tags starts, tag data will be stored in the internal buffer.
        Attention:
        When sets Repeat parameter to 255(0xFF), the anti-collision algorithm is optimized for applications with small tag quantity, which provide better efficiency and less response time.
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF Public Address)
        btRepeat - Repeat time of inventory round. When Repeat = 255, The inventory duration is minimized. For example, if the RF field only has one or two tags, the inventory duration could be only 30-50 mS, this function provides a possibility for fast antenna switch applications on multi-ant devices.
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • readTag

        public final int readTag(byte btReadId,
                         byte btMemBank,
                         byte btWordAdd,
                         byte btWordCnt,
                         byte[] btAryPassWord)
        Read Tag.
        Attention:
        If two tags have the same EPC, but different read data, then these two tags are considered different tags.
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF Public Address)
        btMemBank - Tag memory bank(0x00:RESERVED, 0x01:EPC, 0x02:TID, 0x03:USER)
        btWordAdd - Read start address,please see the tag's spec for more information.
        btWordCnt - Read data length,Data length in WORD(16bits) unit. Please see the tag's spec for more information.
        btAryPassWord - Access password,4 bytes.
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • realTimeInventory

        public final int realTimeInventory(byte btReadId,
                                   byte btRepeat)
        Inventory Tag(Read Time Mode).
        Attention:
        The hardware has a dual CPU architecture, main CPU is responsible for tag inventory, and assistant CPU is responsible for data management. Inventory and data transfer are parallel and simultaneous. So the data transfer via serial port doesn't affect the efficiency of reader.
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF Public Address)
        btRepeat - Repeat time of inventory round. When Repeat = 255, The inventory duration is minimized. For example, if the RF field only has one or two tags, the inventory duration could be only 30-50 mS, this function provides a possibility for fast antenna switch applications on multi-ant devices.
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • fastSwitchAntInventory

        public final int fastSwitchAntInventory(byte btReadId,
                                        byte btA,
                                        byte btStayA,
                                        byte btB,
                                        byte btStayB,
                                        byte btC,
                                        byte btStayC,
                                        byte btD,
                                        byte btStayD,
                                        byte btInterval,
                                        byte btRepeat)
        Fast Switch Antenna Mode.
        Attention:
        The hardware has a dual CPU architecture, main CPU is responsible for tag inventory, and assistant CPU is responsible for data management. Inventory and data transfer are parallel and simultaneous. So the data transfer via serial port doesn't affect the efficiency of reader.
        In massive tag applications, please use cmd_real_time_inventory command which is more effective for large tag quantity applications.
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF Public Address)
        btA - First working ant (00 - 03). If set this byte above 03 means ignore it.
        btStayA - Inventory round for an antenna.
        btB - Second working ant (00 - 03). If set this byte above 03 means ignore it.
        btStayB - Inventory round for an antenna.
        btC - Third working ant (00 - 03). If set this byte above 03 means ignore it.
        btStayC - Inventory round for an antenna.
        btD - Fourth working ant (00 - 03). If set this byte above 03 means ignore it.
        btStayD - Inventory round for an antenna.
        btInterval - Rest time between switching antennas. During the cause of rest, RF output will be cancelled, thus power consumption and heat generation are both reduced.
        btRepeat - Repeat the inventory with above ant switch sequence.
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • setImpinjFastTid

        public final int setImpinjFastTid(byte btReadId,
                                  boolean blnOpen,
                                  boolean blnSave)
        Set Impinj Monza FastTID.
        Attention:
        This function is only affective for some of Impinj Monza tag types.
        This function improves the performance of identifying tag's TID.
        When this function takes effect, tag's TID will be included to tag's EPC, therefore, tag's EPC will be altered; the original data (PC + EPC) will be changed to altered PC + EPC + EPC's CRC + TID.
        If error occurred during identifying TID, only the original data (PC + EPC) will be sent.
        If you don't need this function, please turn it off, otherwise there will be unnecessary time consumption.
        This command doesn't store the status to internal flash. After reset or power on, the value stored in flash will be restored.
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF public address)
        blnOpen - Whether to open FastTID
        blnSave - Whether to store in FLASH
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • getInventoryBuffer

        public final int getInventoryBuffer(byte btReadId)
        Get tag data and keep buffer.
        Attention:
        The data in the buffer won't be lost after execution of this command.
        If the cmd_inventory is executed again, the tag data escalate in the buffer.
        Other 18000-6C commands can clear the buffer.
        参数:
        btReadId - Reader Address(0xFF Public Address)
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1

      • setTagMask

        public final int setTagMask(byte btReadId,
                            byte btMaskNo,
                            byte btTarget,
                            byte btAction,
                            byte btMembank,
                            byte btStartAdd,
                            byte btMaskLen,
                            byte[] maskValue)
        Set the mask filter the Tag.
        参数:
        btReadId - The reader address.
        btMaskNo - The mask No include(0x00,0x01,0x02,0x03,0x04),you set different mask via the mask No.
        btTarget - Set the inventory way(s0,s1,s2 or s3),you must use you set target to inventory the tag.
        btAction - The match tag or not Action,you can see the detail of this command.
        btMembank - The select mask region,EPC,TID or USER.
        btStartAdd - The mask start address(according to bit).
        btMaskLen - The mask length (according to bit).
        maskValue - The mask value.
        返回:
        Succeeded :0, Failed:-1
